1. Retrieve Data tools (SQL Query)

Name : get_employee_by_id
Execution Point: On Demand
Description: "Look up one employee's full record by employee number (EMPNO)."
Parameters: P_EMPNO — NUMBER, required
SQL Query:

SELECT empno, ename, job, mgr, hiredate, sal, comm, deptno
FROM   emp_d
WHERE  empno = :P_EMPNO
/

Name : search_employees
Execution Point: On Demand
Description: "Search employees by partial name, job title, and/or department. Any parameter can be left null."
Parameters: P_NAME VARCHAR2 (optional), P_JOB VARCHAR2 (optional), P_DEPTNO NUMBER (optional)
SQL Query:

SELECT empno, ename, job, mgr, hiredate, sal, comm, deptno
FROM   emp_d
WHERE  (:P_NAME   IS NULL OR UPPER(ename) LIKE '%'||UPPER(:P_NAME)||'%')
AND    (:P_JOB    IS NULL OR UPPER(job)   =  UPPER(:P_JOB))
AND    (:P_DEPTNO IS NULL OR deptno       =  :P_DEPTNO)
ORDER  BY ename
/

Name : list_departments
Execution Point: Augment System Prompt (small, cheap, useful context up front)
Description: "Full list of departments — id, name, location."
Parameters: none
SQL Query:

SELECT deptno, dname, loc FROM dept_d ORDER BY deptno
/

Name : get_department_salary_summary
Execution Point: On Demand
Description: "Headcount and salary stats (avg/min/max, total commission) for one department, or all departments if DEPTNO is null."
Parameters: P_DEPTNO NUMBER (optional)
SQL Query:

SELECT d.deptno, d.dname,
       COUNT(e.empno)               AS headcount,
       ROUND(AVG(e.sal), 2)         AS avg_sal,
       MIN(e.sal)                   AS min_sal,
       MAX(e.sal)                   AS max_sal,
       SUM(NVL(e.comm, 0))          AS total_comm
FROM   dept_d d
LEFT   JOIN emp_d e ON e.deptno = d.deptno
WHERE  (:P_DEPTNO IS NULL OR d.deptno = :P_DEPTNO)
GROUP  BY d.deptno, d.dname
ORDER  BY d.deptno
/


2. Retrieve Data tool (Function Body returning CLOB)

Name : get_org_chart
Execution Point: On Demand
Description: "Text-tree organization chart showing manager → direct-report relationships across all employees."
Parameters: none
Function Body (returns CLOB):

DECLARE
  l_result CLOB;
BEGIN
  FOR r IN (
    SELECT LPAD(' ', (LEVEL - 1) * 2) || ename || ' — ' || job AS line
    FROM   emp_d
    START WITH mgr IS NULL
    CONNECT BY PRIOR empno = mgr
    ORDER SIBLINGS BY ename
  ) LOOP
    l_result := l_result || r.line || CHR(10);
  END LOOP;
  RETURN l_result;
END;
/

3. Execute Server-side Code tools (PL/SQL) — full CRUD

Name : create_employee
Execution Point: On Demand
Description: "Hire a new employee. HIREDATE format is YYYY-MM-DD; defaults to today if omitted."
Parameters:
P_EMPNO - NUMBER - Required
P_ENAME - VARCHAR2 -Required 
P_JOB - VARCHAR2 - Required
P_MGR - NUMBER - Optional
P_HIREDATE - VARCHAR2 - Optional
P_SAL -NUMBER -Required
P_COMM - NUMBER -Optional
P_DEPTNO- NUMBER -Required


PL/SQL Code:

BEGIN
  INSERT INTO emp_d (empno, ename, job, mgr, hiredate, sal, comm, deptno)
  VALUES (:P_EMPNO, :P_ENAME, :P_JOB, :P_MGR,
          NVL(TO_DATE(:P_HIREDATE, 'YYYY-MM-DD'), TRUNC(SYSDATE)),
          :P_SAL, :P_COMM, :P_DEPTNO);
END;
/

Name : update_employee_salary
Description: "Change an employee's salary and, optionally, commission."
Parameters: 
P_EMPNO - NUMBER - Required
P_NEW_SAL - NUMBER - Required
P_NEW_COMM - NUMBER - Optional

PL/SQL Code:

BEGIN
  UPDATE emp_d
  SET    sal  = :P_NEW_SAL,
         comm = NVL(:P_NEW_COMM, comm)
  WHERE  empno = :P_EMPNO;

  IF SQL%ROWCOUNT = 0 THEN
    apex_ai.set_tool_result('No employee found with EMPNO ' || :P_EMPNO, p_success => FALSE);
  END IF;
END;
/

Name : transfer_employee
Description: "Move an employee to a different department and, optionally, reassign their manager."
Parameters: 
P_EMPNO - NUMBER - required
P_NEW_DEPTNO - NUMBER - Required
P_NEW_MGR - NUMBER - Optional
PL/SQL Code:

BEGIN
  UPDATE emp_d
  SET    deptno = :P_NEW_DEPTNO,
         mgr    = NVL(:P_NEW_MGR, mgr)
  WHERE  empno  = :P_EMPNO;
END;
/


Name : delete_employee
Description: "Permanently remove an employee record. Destructive — confirm with the user first."
Requires Confirmation: Yes — Title: "Delete Employee", Message: "This permanently removes the employee record. Continue?"
Parameters: 
P_EMPNO - NUMBER - Required
PL/SQL Code:

BEGIN
  DELETE FROM emp_d WHERE empno = :P_EMPNO;
  IF SQL%ROWCOUNT = 0 THEN
    apex_ai.set_tool_result('No employee found with EMPNO ' || :P_EMPNO, p_success => FALSE);
  END IF;
END;
/

Name : create_department
Description: "Create a new department."
Parameters: 
P_DEPTNO - NUMBER - Required
P_DNAME - VARCHAR2 - Required
P_LOC - VARCHAR2 - Optional

PL/SQL Code:

BEGIN
  INSERT INTO dept_d (deptno, dname, loc) VALUES (:P_DEPTNO, :P_DNAME, :P_LOC);
END;
/

Name : update_department
Description: "Rename a department or change its location."
Parameters: 
P_DEPTNO - NUMBER - Required
P_DNAME - VARCHAR2 - Optional
P_LOC - VARCHAR2 - Optional
PL/SQL Code:

BEGIN
  UPDATE dept_d
  SET    dname = NVL(:P_DNAME, dname),
         loc   = NVL(:P_LOC, loc)
  WHERE  deptno = :P_DEPTNO;
END;
/

Name : delete_department
Description: "Delete a department. Blocked if employees are still assigned to it."
Requires Confirmation: Yes — Title: "Delete Department", Message: "This permanently removes the department. Continue?"
Parameters: 
P_DEPTNO - NUMBER - Required
PL/SQL Code:

DECLARE
  l_cnt NUMBER;
BEGIN
  SELECT COUNT(*) INTO l_cnt FROM emp_d WHERE deptno = :P_DEPTNO;
  IF l_cnt > 0 THEN
    apex_ai.set_tool_result(
      l_cnt || ' employee(s) are still assigned to this department. Reassign or remove them first.',
      p_success => FALSE);
  ELSE
    DELETE FROM dept_d WHERE deptno = :P_DEPTNO;
  END IF;
END;
/


4. Execute Client-side Code tool (JavaScript)

Name : confirm_destructive_action
Type: Execute Client-side Code
Description: "Shows a browser confirmation dialog before any delete tool runs. Always call this before delete_employee or delete_department and only proceed if the result is confirmed = true."
Parameters: P_MESSAGE VARCHAR2 (required)
JavaScript Code:


javascriptreturn new Promise((resolve) => {
  apex.message.confirm(this.data.P_MESSAGE, function(okPressed) {
    resolve({ confirmed: okPressed });
  });
});


Suggested Routing Instructions (on the AI Agent, not per-tool)

Always call list_departments and get_department_salary_summary before answering
questions about department headcount or pay.
Before calling delete_employee or delete_department, first call
confirm_destructive_action and only proceed if confirmed = true.
Never fabricate EMPNO or DEPTNO values — look them up with search_employees or
list_departments first if the user doesn't provide them.
